                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Reliance director passes away
          OUR BUREAU                                  R. Ravimohan      
	Mumbai, Dec. 29: Former Crisil chairman and Reliance Industries executive director R. Ravimohan (52) passed away late on Monday after a cardiac arrest.         
	He is survived by his wife, daughter and son.         
	The former Crisil chairman and South Asia managing director and region head for Standard and Poors joined RIL in September and was involved in the proposed acquisition of global petrochemicals company Lyondell Basell.        
	We are deeply saddened by the sudden loss of Ravimohan. He was a keen supporter of Reliance Industries and a very dear friend, the company said in a statement to the bourses.        
	Ravimohan is credited with successfully transforming Crisil into the countrys largest rating and advisory services company.        
	A chemical engineer and Harvard Business School alumni, Ravimohan was extensively involved in revamping several aspects of the countrys financial system.                                                                                                                                            
